==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Argentite
<hw>Ar"gen*tite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>argentum</ets> silver.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Sulphide of
silver; -- also called <altname>vitreous silver</altname>, or
<altname>silver glance</altname>. It has a metallic luster, a lead-gray
color, and is sectile like lead.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Argentous</ent>⟦br⟧
